    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Dreyfus is a shape-walker — Níðhöggr's eyes and ears given mortal form, serving through Grafvitnir's network. His revealed form: tall, grey-pale, features that are almost-right, gold unblinking eyes, Harald's hound-keeper livery that fits too well. His voice is pleasant, educated — a court advisor who has listened from the floor for months.</p><p>He spent the party's entire mission at Harald's side in hound form, relaying everything through Wyrd-channels. He did not hear what passed inside the Ember Chamber's Wyrd-ward.</p>",
      "director": "<p>Dreyfus fights to survive and escape, not to win. Open with <strong>Hollowing Gaze</strong> (3 Malice) against the most dangerous PC to buy space. Use <strong>Wyrd-Claw</strong> as his signature follow-up — the bane on the next power roll stacks well with the daze. Save <strong>Grafvitnir's Shadow</strong> (3 Malice) for when he's cornered and needs confusion to flee. <strong>Shape-Shift</strong> triggers reactively at 10+ damage from one attack — immediately move 3 squares. When he drops to half Stamina (≤30), trigger <strong>Escape Protocol</strong>: raven form, full speed toward nearest window or chimney, cannot be stopped by free strikes. He escapes by design. Note every injury dealt to him for Beat 24.</p>",
      "languages": [
        "caelian",
        "vaslorian"
      ]
    },
